## Transactions (Toshl MCP)

Financial transactions are synced to [toshl.com](https://toshl.com) and accessible via the `toshl` MCP server.

Use the Toshl MCP to:
- Fetch recent transactions and categorise spending
- Identify trends across income and expense categories
- Answer questions like "how much did I spend on X last month"
- Compare spending across time periods
- Check account balances and net worth snapshots

## Financial Planning Workflows

### Pension Review
- Cross-reference the pension providers listed above with current contribution rates
- Note that pension schemes from previous employers may have been consolidated — check the notes above for merger history
- When researching a provider (Aviva, Davy, etc.), use web search for current fund performance data

### Spending Analysis
1. Use the Toshl MCP to pull transactions for the relevant period
2. Group by category to identify the largest expense areas
3. Compare against prior periods to surface trends
4. Flag any anomalous or unrecognised transactions for review

### Savings Goals
- Use Toshl budget data to measure progress against savings targets
- Identify discretionary categories where spending could be reduced

## Safety

- Never store or output provider names, raw account numbers, PINs, or passwords
- Pension provider details above are injected at apply time from 1Password — do not hardcode them
- Treat all financial data as sensitive — do not include it in commit messages, PR descriptions, or logs
